{"type":"message","id":"1a13618a","parentId":"e50cc405","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:45:17.139Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_izw74Ab4h3QwmTWpVYuuHCbv|fc_0c3abcc532bcb4ed0169cd59a9e88c81918c1166af7a9b242c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1 (unknown) — I run on caffeine, JSON5, and the audacity of \"it worked on my machine.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1660,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1 (unknown) — I run on caffeine, JSON5, and the audacity of \"it worked on my machine.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775065517137}}
{"type":"message","id":"c070c5ad","parentId":"1a13618a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:45:24.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Listo: ajusté la estrategia principal por archivo y ahora sincronizo los cron vivos para que OpenClaw los tome bien.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c3abcc532bcb4ed0169cd59aea8cc81919f0f82a269df8e4c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_jYuRtxGExwjmfvgCEy8tpeER|fc_0c3abcc532bcb4ed0169cd59af654881918f0ed5d941eeba71","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"03b29602-b584-4ec0-9241-b0d74393cc82","patch":{"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Revisa el Tasks Tracker de Notion (DB id: 32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7, dentro de la página 'Atlas OS - Home' id: 32f0a0b1-97cc-8115-9e62-ec8765ad533c) con enfoque liviano. Solo procesa: (1) tareas en estado Next; (2) tareas Blocked o Waiting que lleven tiempo o necesiten destrabe; (3) inbox principal si la primera tabla visible trae responsable claro y acción inmediata. Máximo 3 tareas por corrida. Para cada una: coordina al agente responsable con una instrucción concreta, exige primer paso o bloqueo explícito, y no marques Done sin confirmación real de entrega. Si no hay cambios relevantes, no inventes trabajo. Al final envía a WhatsApp +573183718246 un resumen de máximo 5 bullets: qué moviste, qué quedó bloqueado y cuál es el siguiente paso.","timeoutSeconds":900}}},"partialJson":"{\"action\":\"update\",\"jobId\":\"03b29602-b584-4ec0-9241-b0d74393cc82\",\"patch\":{\"payload\":{\"kind\":\"agentTurn\",\"message\":\"Revisa el Tasks Tracker de Notion (DB id: 32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7, dentro de la página 'Atlas OS - Home' id: 32f0a0b1-97cc-8115-9e62-ec8765ad533c) con enfoque liviano. Solo procesa: (1) tareas en estado Next; (2) tareas Blocked o Waiting que lleven tiempo o necesiten destrabe; (3) inbox principal si la primera tabla visible trae responsable claro y acción inmediata. Máximo 3 tareas por corrida. Para cada una: coordina al agente responsable con una instrucción concreta, exige primer paso o bloqueo explícito, y no marques Done sin confirmación real de entrega. Si no hay cambios relevantes, no inventes trabajo. Al final envía a WhatsApp +573183718246 un resumen de máximo 5 bullets: qué moviste, qué quedó bloqueado y cuál es el siguiente paso.\",\"timeoutSeconds\":900}}}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":702,"output":309,"cacheRead":51072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52083,"cost":{"input":0.001755,"output":0.004635,"cacheRead":0.012768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.019158}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775065517140,"responseId":"resp_0c3abcc532bcb4ed0169cd59ad5e8c8191847effb00709818d"}}
